WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.356 align:middle line:90%
[SWOOSHING SOUND]

00:00:04.356 --> 00:00:08.712 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.712 --> 00:00:13.560 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:15.840 align:middle line:84%
>> My entire life just
came crashing down.

00:00:15.840 --> 00:00:19.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:22.225 align:middle line:84%
I had lost my home
due to foreclosure.

00:00:22.225 --> 00:00:28.410 align:middle line:90%


00:00:28.410 --> 00:00:29.730 align:middle line:90%
I was six figures in debt.

00:00:29.730 --> 00:00:32.750 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.750 --> 00:00:36.220 align:middle line:90%
My boyfriend was an alcoholic.

00:00:36.220 --> 00:00:37.440 align:middle line:90%
That relationship broke up.

00:00:37.440 --> 00:00:40.650 align:middle line:90%


00:00:40.650 --> 00:00:43.260 align:middle line:84%
And I had a very
serious blood clot close

00:00:43.260 --> 00:00:45.030 align:middle line:90%
to my heart and lungs.

00:00:45.030 --> 00:00:47.250 align:middle line:84%
And so I had to go into
emergency treatment for that.

00:00:47.250 --> 00:00:50.330 align:middle line:90%


00:00:50.330 --> 00:00:54.830 align:middle line:84%
As everything was just crashing
down, I just fell to my knees.

00:00:54.830 --> 00:00:58.040 align:middle line:84%
I just didn't know how I
was going to get through it.

00:00:58.040 --> 00:00:59.570 align:middle line:90%
I really hit rock bottom.

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:02.860 align:middle line:90%


00:01:02.860 --> 00:01:06.970 align:middle line:84%
I was lying in my bed and
just crying, crying, crying,

00:01:06.970 --> 00:01:11.800 align:middle line:84%
crying all by myself,
rolled up in a ball.

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:15.020 align:middle line:84%
The story that I kept on telling
myself is, how did this happen?

00:01:15.020 --> 00:01:16.570 align:middle line:84%
How am I going to
get out of this?

00:01:16.570 --> 00:01:17.530 align:middle line:90%
What am I going to do?

00:01:17.530 --> 00:01:20.630 align:middle line:90%


00:01:20.630 --> 00:01:22.630 align:middle line:90%
I felt really helpless.

00:01:22.630 --> 00:01:26.340 align:middle line:84%
And for a really brief moment,
I wanted to end it all.

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:29.520 align:middle line:90%


00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:31.410 align:middle line:90%
I just wanted the pain to stop.

00:01:31.410 --> 00:01:34.290 align:middle line:90%


00:01:34.290 --> 00:01:36.550 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know how to
make that pain stop.

00:01:36.550 --> 00:01:39.620 align:middle line:90%


00:01:39.620 --> 00:01:41.120 align:middle line:84%
And so what I
allowed myself to do

00:01:41.120 --> 00:01:46.600 align:middle line:84%
is I just allowed myself
to just cry it all out.

00:01:46.600 --> 00:01:49.510 align:middle line:84%
And after crying,
I got out of bed.

00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:52.750 align:middle line:90%


00:01:52.750 --> 00:01:57.260 align:middle line:84%
I walked around the
bed to the window.

00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:03.530 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking outside
the window when I said,

00:02:03.530 --> 00:02:06.620 align:middle line:84%
I don't know why
this is happening.

00:02:06.620 --> 00:02:11.360 align:middle line:84%
But one thing I know for
sure, something big, something

00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:15.230 align:middle line:84%
huge something
way bigger than me

00:02:15.230 --> 00:02:17.630 align:middle line:90%
is going to come out of this.

00:02:17.630 --> 00:02:20.720 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm not going through
all this stuff for nothing.

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:24.480 align:middle line:90%


00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:28.020 align:middle line:90%
It was like a declaration.

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:35.474 align:middle line:84%
It was an intention I
sent out to the universe.

00:02:35.474 --> 00:03:07.087 align:middle line:90%


00:03:07.087 --> 00:03:09.420 align:middle line:84%
>> You're going to go through
challenges in life one way

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:10.870 align:middle line:90%
or another.

00:03:10.870 --> 00:03:15.500 align:middle line:84%
In the hero's journey, we
would call this the initiation.

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:17.760 align:middle line:84%
The hero's journey is
this famous narrative that

00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:20.592 align:middle line:90%
really applies to all of us.

00:03:20.592 --> 00:03:22.800 align:middle line:84%
And there are three main
parts of the hero's journey.

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:26.020 align:middle line:84%
There's a separation, an
initiation, and a return.

00:03:26.020 --> 00:03:28.020 align:middle line:84%
And the beautiful thing
about the hero's journey

00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:28.990 align:middle line:90%
is it's cyclical.

00:03:28.990 --> 00:03:31.080 align:middle line:84%
It's something that
happens on macro cycles

00:03:31.080 --> 00:03:32.520 align:middle line:90%
and it happens on micro cycles.

00:03:32.520 --> 00:03:34.770 align:middle line:84%
And it's not, at one point,
we've just reached it

00:03:34.770 --> 00:03:36.270 align:middle line:90%
and we're done and we finished.

00:03:36.270 --> 00:03:38.320 align:middle line:84%
It's something that we're
always moving through.

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:40.530 align:middle line:84%
And so here are a
couple interesting parts

00:03:40.530 --> 00:03:43.530 align:middle line:84%
of the hero's journey that I
feel that we as individuals can

00:03:43.530 --> 00:03:47.340 align:middle line:84%
relate to being somewhere
on the journey at any given

00:03:47.340 --> 00:03:48.960 align:middle line:90%
point in our lives.

00:03:48.960 --> 00:03:50.640 align:middle line:84%
The first thing that
happens is we're

00:03:50.640 --> 00:03:54.210 align:middle line:84%
on a path, a path that maybe
someone else decided was

00:03:54.210 --> 00:03:56.220 align:middle line:84%
ours to take, parents,
society, school.

00:03:56.220 --> 00:03:58.470 align:middle line:84%
And we realized we're meant
to be on a different path.

00:03:58.470 --> 00:04:01.403 align:middle line:84%
And so when we first realized
we were meant to be on a path,

00:04:01.403 --> 00:04:02.820 align:middle line:84%
this is what Joseph
Campbell would

00:04:02.820 --> 00:04:06.090 align:middle line:84%
call the CTA, the Call To
Action or the Call To Adventure.

00:04:06.090 --> 00:04:08.120 align:middle line:84%
He would say, that
the phone is ringing.

00:04:08.120 --> 00:04:10.620 align:middle line:84%
And what's fascinating about
this part of the hero's journey

00:04:10.620 --> 00:04:15.046 align:middle line:84%
is most people don't pick
up the phone right away.

00:04:15.046 --> 00:04:17.541 align:middle line:84%
This is where it actually
gets a little bit sad,

00:04:17.541 --> 00:04:20.733 align:middle line:84%
because some people will wait an
entire lifetime not picking up

00:04:20.733 --> 00:04:21.533 align:middle line:90%
their phone.

00:04:21.533 --> 00:04:24.028 align:middle line:84%
They'll hear the phone ringing
but they won't pick it up.

00:04:24.028 --> 00:04:26.523 align:middle line:84%
And those are the people that
are on their deathbed saying,

00:04:26.523 --> 00:04:28.898 align:middle line:84%
I wish I'd had the courage to
live a life true to myself.

00:04:28.898 --> 00:04:31.014 align:middle line:84%
What they're saying is,
I wish I had the courage

00:04:31.014 --> 00:04:34.008 align:middle line:90%
to pick up the phone.

00:04:34.008 --> 00:04:37.501 align:middle line:84%
>> Individuals,
they grow two ways.

00:04:37.501 --> 00:04:42.491 align:middle line:84%
They grow through pain, or
they grow through insight.

00:04:42.491 --> 00:04:45.485 align:middle line:84%
Individuals either
get sick and tired,

00:04:45.485 --> 00:04:47.481 align:middle line:84%
because their experience
is being determined

00:04:47.481 --> 00:04:48.898 align:middle line:84%
by the environment
in which we are

00:04:48.898 --> 00:04:52.471 align:middle line:84%
in, the conversations,
by the social milieu,

00:04:52.471 --> 00:04:54.966 align:middle line:84%
by whatever's going
on in society.

00:04:54.966 --> 00:04:56.463 align:middle line:90%
It's an imprint.

00:04:56.463 --> 00:04:59.207 align:middle line:84%
And so in the
beginning, we learn how

00:04:59.207 --> 00:05:00.954 align:middle line:90%
to survive with the imprint.

00:05:00.954 --> 00:05:04.447 align:middle line:84%
And then we learn how to
adapt with the imprint.

00:05:04.447 --> 00:05:07.441 align:middle line:84%
And then at some
point in our life,

00:05:07.441 --> 00:05:12.431 align:middle line:84%
either through pain, suffering,
or through tremendous insight,

00:05:12.431 --> 00:05:13.622 align:middle line:90%
we learn to transform.

00:05:13.622 --> 00:05:15.840 align:middle line:84%
We learn to go
beyond the imprint.

00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:18.150 align:middle line:84%
And at some point,
we all have to be

00:05:18.150 --> 00:05:21.600 align:middle line:84%
taught that there's
something about us,

00:05:21.600 --> 00:05:26.370 align:middle line:84%
something gifted, something
intrinsic within you

00:05:26.370 --> 00:05:29.770 align:middle line:84%
that no one else has
the way you have it.

00:05:29.770 --> 00:05:33.240 align:middle line:90%


00:05:33.240 --> 00:05:36.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Most people, when they're
going through something

00:05:36.330 --> 00:05:39.690 align:middle line:84%
that's debilitating, they'll
ask a disempowering question.

00:05:39.690 --> 00:05:43.140 align:middle line:84%
They'll ask from a
victim state, why me?

00:05:43.140 --> 00:05:45.090 align:middle line:90%
Who's to blame?

00:05:45.090 --> 00:05:46.680 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong?

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:48.750 align:middle line:84%
And the mind would
just go wrap it

00:05:48.750 --> 00:05:50.330 align:middle line:90%
with those kind of questions.

00:05:50.330 --> 00:05:51.540 align:middle line:90%
They don't take you anywhere.

00:05:51.540 --> 00:05:53.670 align:middle line:84%
They take you on
a downward spiral,

00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:57.800 align:middle line:84%
or you will end up
mining the database

00:05:57.800 --> 00:06:00.230 align:middle line:90%
of human consciousness.

00:06:00.230 --> 00:06:03.358 align:middle line:84%
You'll just pull in all the
frequency of all the suffering

00:06:03.358 --> 00:06:04.650 align:middle line:90%
that's happening on the planet.

00:06:04.650 --> 00:06:07.300 align:middle line:90%


00:06:07.300 --> 00:06:10.570 align:middle line:84%
>> We are
meaning-making machines.

00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:12.520 align:middle line:84%
Everything that we've
experienced in life

00:06:12.520 --> 00:06:15.760 align:middle line:84%
is exactly what we
needed to experience.

00:06:15.760 --> 00:06:18.585 align:middle line:84%
Everything we've been through
has been divinely orchestrated

00:06:18.585 --> 00:06:20.960 align:middle line:84%
in some way to bring us to
this present moment right now.

00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:24.010 align:middle line:84%
So if you are grateful
for this moment,

00:06:24.010 --> 00:06:25.630 align:middle line:84%
you must, by
definition, be grateful

00:06:25.630 --> 00:06:27.088 align:middle line:84%
for every single
moment that you've

00:06:27.088 --> 00:06:29.020 align:middle line:84%
been through that got
you to this moment,

00:06:29.020 --> 00:06:31.190 align:middle line:84%
and every single one
that unfolds beyond that.

00:06:31.190 --> 00:06:33.580 align:middle line:84%
And so the meaning is
something that we can

00:06:33.580 --> 00:06:35.350 align:middle line:90%
place on events and experience.

00:06:35.350 --> 00:06:37.937 align:middle line:84%
So if we feel like
something negative happened

00:06:37.937 --> 00:06:40.270 align:middle line:84%
to us in our lives, we don't
have to see it as negative.

00:06:40.270 --> 00:06:42.687 align:middle line:84%
If we feel like we're going
through something challenging,

00:06:42.687 --> 00:06:45.190 align:middle line:84%
we get to actually apply this,
this meaning-making principle

00:06:45.190 --> 00:06:48.680 align:middle line:84%
to what we're going
through right now.

00:06:48.680 --> 00:06:52.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Once I did that declaration,
it was like I sent the message

00:06:52.520 --> 00:06:56.360 align:middle line:84%
out to god, universe,
whatever you believe in.

00:06:56.360 --> 00:06:59.750 align:middle line:90%
And it got the wheels in motion.

00:06:59.750 --> 00:07:04.010 align:middle line:84%
And about a week later, I
was still in that house.

00:07:04.010 --> 00:07:05.030 align:middle line:90%
We hadn't lost it yet.

00:07:05.030 --> 00:07:07.530 align:middle line:90%
We were about to lose it.

00:07:07.530 --> 00:07:10.790 align:middle line:84%
And as I was walking up
the stairs of that house,

00:07:10.790 --> 00:07:14.120 align:middle line:84%
I got to the landing, and I
said, I really get it now.

00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:17.480 align:middle line:84%
I'm going through all this
stuff because my mission in life

00:07:17.480 --> 00:07:20.265 align:middle line:84%
is to help others bounce
back from difficult times.

00:07:20.265 --> 00:07:24.190 align:middle line:90%


00:07:24.190 --> 00:07:28.200 align:middle line:84%
I found a meaning that
is bigger than me,

00:07:28.200 --> 00:07:30.240 align:middle line:84%
that was something
like it was that light

00:07:30.240 --> 00:07:31.718 align:middle line:90%
at the end of the tunnel.

00:07:31.718 --> 00:07:32.760 align:middle line:90%
And it was really bright.

00:07:32.760 --> 00:07:34.350 align:middle line:90%
And I knew it was there.

00:07:34.350 --> 00:07:36.750 align:middle line:84%
And I needed to find my
way outside that tunnel.

00:07:36.750 --> 00:07:50.115 align:middle line:90%


00:07:50.115 --> 00:07:53.590 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:53.590 --> 00:07:56.682 align:middle line:84%
>> I had a really
idyllic childhood.

00:07:56.682 --> 00:07:59.390 align:middle line:84%
Our house overlooked this
really awesome surf break.

00:07:59.390 --> 00:08:02.310 align:middle line:90%


00:08:02.310 --> 00:08:04.602 align:middle line:84%
Before school every morning,
I would go out surfing.

00:08:04.602 --> 00:08:06.810 align:middle line:84%
And would come home from
school, I would go for surf.

00:08:06.810 --> 00:08:10.540 align:middle line:90%


00:08:10.540 --> 00:08:11.640 align:middle line:90%
I loved surfing.

00:08:11.640 --> 00:08:13.220 align:middle line:90%
That was where I had fun.

00:08:13.220 --> 00:08:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And I'd go for
runs every morning

00:08:14.750 --> 00:08:15.870 align:middle line:90%
before school with my dad.

00:08:15.870 --> 00:08:18.850 align:middle line:90%


00:08:18.850 --> 00:08:20.890 align:middle line:84%
I've always been a
very physical person.

00:08:20.890 --> 00:08:23.260 align:middle line:84%
And for me, being active,
that's my therapy.

00:08:23.260 --> 00:08:26.380 align:middle line:90%


00:08:26.380 --> 00:08:28.200 align:middle line:84%
I was living in the
middle of Australia.

00:08:28.200 --> 00:08:31.210 align:middle line:84%
I had this really awesome
job at this diamond mine.

00:08:31.210 --> 00:08:33.610 align:middle line:90%
I found my job quite stressful.

00:08:33.610 --> 00:08:36.137 align:middle line:84%
And I was away from the coast
for the first time in my life,

00:08:36.137 --> 00:08:36.970 align:middle line:90%
so I started to run.

00:08:36.970 --> 00:08:40.220 align:middle line:90%


00:08:40.220 --> 00:08:43.650 align:middle line:84%
And so I'd do these really
big runs after work.

00:08:43.650 --> 00:08:45.320 align:middle line:84%
I was always great
at running at school.

00:08:45.320 --> 00:08:48.080 align:middle line:84%
I was always a good
cross-country runner.

00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:49.940 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't because I was fast.

00:08:49.940 --> 00:08:51.050 align:middle line:90%
I just don't stop.

00:08:51.050 --> 00:08:52.040 align:middle line:90%
It's a mental game.

00:08:52.040 --> 00:08:54.110 align:middle line:84%
Because when you're
on a really long run,

00:08:54.110 --> 00:08:55.912 align:middle line:84%
your body gives up
but your mind doesn't.

00:08:55.912 --> 00:08:57.620 align:middle line:84%
And your mind has got
to be strong enough

00:08:57.620 --> 00:08:59.870 align:middle line:84%
to say, no, you've just
got be able to kick on.

00:08:59.870 --> 00:09:01.453 align:middle line:84%
You've just got to
take the next step.

00:09:01.453 --> 00:09:03.920 align:middle line:90%


00:09:03.920 --> 00:09:05.700 align:middle line:84%
I've always really
liked challenges.

00:09:05.700 --> 00:09:09.770 align:middle line:84%
So I'd sign up to
do an ultramarathon.

00:09:09.770 --> 00:09:10.670 align:middle line:90%
I was excited.

00:09:10.670 --> 00:09:12.450 align:middle line:90%
It was another challenge for me.

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:15.830 align:middle line:84%
It was something to get to learn
a little bit more about myself

00:09:15.830 --> 00:09:17.230 align:middle line:90%
and what type of person I was.

00:09:17.230 --> 00:09:20.270 align:middle line:90%


00:09:20.270 --> 00:09:22.490 align:middle line:84%
The start of the run, we
were in outback Australia.

00:09:22.490 --> 00:09:25.130 align:middle line:84%
And summer had just ended,
so it was really, really hot.

00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:29.170 align:middle line:90%


00:09:29.170 --> 00:09:31.120 align:middle line:90%
I heard this noise.

00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:32.860 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that
the next checkpoint

00:09:32.860 --> 00:09:35.630 align:middle line:84%
was over the other
side of the highway.

00:09:35.630 --> 00:09:39.605 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought the noise was
the sound of road trains coming

00:09:39.605 --> 00:09:40.405 align:middle line:90%
down the highway.

00:09:40.405 --> 00:09:43.815 align:middle line:90%


00:09:43.815 --> 00:09:44.940 align:middle line:90%
That kind of spurred me on.

00:09:44.940 --> 00:09:46.398 align:middle line:84%
And I got this real
rush of energy,

00:09:46.398 --> 00:09:48.513 align:middle line:84%
like, yep, almost a
checkpoint through.

00:09:48.513 --> 00:09:49.430 align:middle line:90%
You've got this, girl.

00:09:49.430 --> 00:09:52.510 align:middle line:90%


00:09:52.510 --> 00:09:56.160 align:middle line:84%
As I ran through this gorge,
I noticed these other runners

00:09:56.160 --> 00:09:57.260 align:middle line:90%
around me.

00:09:57.260 --> 00:10:00.240 align:middle line:84%
And they were all looking at
this big fire coming really

00:10:00.240 --> 00:10:03.240 align:middle line:90%
quickly through the gorge.

00:10:03.240 --> 00:10:04.110 align:middle line:90%
And I was panicking.

00:10:04.110 --> 00:10:07.100 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know if I was ever
going to make it out alive.

00:10:07.100 --> 00:10:11.050 align:middle line:90%
So I'd actually started to cry.

00:10:11.050 --> 00:10:13.342 align:middle line:84%
What happened next, it
happened so quickly.

00:10:13.342 --> 00:10:14.925 align:middle line:84%
The fire got sucked
through the gorge.

00:10:14.925 --> 00:10:18.350 align:middle line:90%


00:10:18.350 --> 00:10:20.580 align:middle line:84%
And I ended up being
burnt all over my body.

00:10:20.580 --> 00:10:23.800 align:middle line:90%


00:10:23.800 --> 00:10:25.610 align:middle line:90%
I remember thinking, this is it.

00:10:25.610 --> 00:10:26.410 align:middle line:90%
This is how I die.

00:10:26.410 --> 00:10:28.330 align:middle line:84%
I just thought about
how unfair it was,

00:10:28.330 --> 00:10:30.980 align:middle line:84%
and that I never see
anyone I loved ever again.

00:10:30.980 --> 00:10:34.660 align:middle line:90%


00:10:34.660 --> 00:10:37.990 align:middle line:84%
After the fire had passed, I was
still in a shock of disbelief,

00:10:37.990 --> 00:10:40.490 align:middle line:90%
like what just happened?

00:10:40.490 --> 00:10:42.250 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that
I was still standing,

00:10:42.250 --> 00:10:43.167 align:middle line:90%
and I was still alive.

00:10:43.167 --> 00:10:46.320 align:middle line:90%


00:10:46.320 --> 00:10:48.120 align:middle line:84%
The next couple
of hours, I didn't

00:10:48.120 --> 00:10:54.290 align:middle line:84%
know how long it was, time had
dilated, it had constricted.

00:10:54.290 --> 00:10:56.960 align:middle line:84%
But I ended up getting
helicoptered out of that gorge

00:10:56.960 --> 00:10:59.550 align:middle line:84%
about four hours
later after the fire.

00:10:59.550 --> 00:11:02.480 align:middle line:84%
There was a volunteering
ambulance paramedic, who

00:11:02.480 --> 00:11:03.800 align:middle line:90%
was there on site to help me.

00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:04.910 align:middle line:90%
And I recognized her.

00:11:04.910 --> 00:11:05.920 align:middle line:90%
She didn't recognize me.

00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:06.500 align:middle line:90%
She didn't know who I was.

00:11:06.500 --> 00:11:07.300 align:middle line:90%
I said, it's me.

00:11:07.300 --> 00:11:08.112 align:middle line:90%
It's Turia.

00:11:08.112 --> 00:11:09.320 align:middle line:90%
She didn't say anything back.

00:11:09.320 --> 00:11:11.980 align:middle line:84%
But I noticed a tear started
to roll slowly down her face.

00:11:11.980 --> 00:11:15.110 align:middle line:84%
So even though I was in this
state that, yeah, I'm sweet.

00:11:15.110 --> 00:11:17.270 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go to the
hospital and get patched up.

00:11:17.270 --> 00:11:19.670 align:middle line:90%
I'll be back at work on Monday.

00:11:19.670 --> 00:11:23.250 align:middle line:84%
I had this sense that maybe
something bad had happened.

00:11:23.250 --> 00:11:26.737 align:middle line:90%


00:11:26.737 --> 00:11:28.320 align:middle line:84%
And I got transferred
to the hospital.

00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:31.750 align:middle line:90%


00:11:31.750 --> 00:11:34.300 align:middle line:90%
I was put in an induced coma.

00:11:34.300 --> 00:11:37.690 align:middle line:90%


00:11:37.690 --> 00:11:39.310 align:middle line:84%
They performed
escharotomies on me.

00:11:39.310 --> 00:11:41.080 align:middle line:84%
An escharotomy is
when they slashed you

00:11:41.080 --> 00:11:43.420 align:middle line:84%
from the top of your
leg down to your ankle

00:11:43.420 --> 00:11:44.950 align:middle line:90%
to relieve the pressure.

00:11:44.950 --> 00:11:47.860 align:middle line:84%
Because after a burn,
you start to swell up.

00:11:47.860 --> 00:11:50.410 align:middle line:84%
When you're burnt that they
needed to debride your skin.

00:11:50.410 --> 00:11:52.270 align:middle line:84%
And debriding just means
they need to remove

00:11:52.270 --> 00:11:53.470 align:middle line:90%
all of the burnt skin.

00:11:53.470 --> 00:11:57.650 align:middle line:90%


00:11:57.650 --> 00:12:00.350 align:middle line:84%
I think it was almost
maybe two months

00:12:00.350 --> 00:12:04.200 align:middle line:84%
later until I really
realized what had happened.

00:12:04.200 --> 00:12:07.070 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't get a
real insight into it.

00:12:07.070 --> 00:12:11.332 align:middle line:84%
Because one morning this
guy came into my room,

00:12:11.332 --> 00:12:12.540 align:middle line:90%
and I didn't know who he was.

00:12:12.540 --> 00:12:14.510 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh,
good morning, Turia.

00:12:14.510 --> 00:12:15.310 align:middle line:90%
My name's Frank.

00:12:15.310 --> 00:12:17.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm your physiotherapist.

00:12:17.170 --> 00:12:21.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm here to help you
learn how to stand again.

00:12:21.160 --> 00:12:25.480 align:middle line:84%
And he managed to get
me in bed and pull me

00:12:25.480 --> 00:12:26.410 align:middle line:90%
in a sitting position.

00:12:26.410 --> 00:12:27.970 align:middle line:90%
And it was complete agony.

00:12:27.970 --> 00:12:31.920 align:middle line:84%
It was the most pain I've ever
felt in my whole entire life.

00:12:31.920 --> 00:12:34.930 align:middle line:84%
And he pulled me
up onto my feet.

00:12:34.930 --> 00:12:37.197 align:middle line:84%
And I remember
sobbing, just sobbing

00:12:37.197 --> 00:12:39.280 align:middle line:84%
and crying all over his
neck, into his gold chain.

00:12:39.280 --> 00:12:43.150 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that was
really the moment when

00:12:43.150 --> 00:12:47.480 align:middle line:84%
I realized how big
this challenge was

00:12:47.480 --> 00:12:48.280 align:middle line:90%
that I was facing.

00:12:48.280 --> 00:12:51.410 align:middle line:84%
Because I couldn't even
stand up by myself.

00:12:51.410 --> 00:12:57.020 align:middle line:84%
So the thought of being able to
walk again, run again, compete

00:12:57.020 --> 00:13:00.400 align:middle line:84%
again, go back to work, have
a family with my partner,

00:13:00.400 --> 00:13:04.290 align:middle line:84%
those things just seemed
so far away and so,

00:13:04.290 --> 00:13:07.310 align:middle line:84%
so impossible for
me to be able to do.

00:13:07.310 --> 00:13:09.500 align:middle line:90%


00:13:09.500 --> 00:13:13.760 align:middle line:84%
>> The dark side of the soul is
a moment in which you lose all

00:13:13.760 --> 00:13:18.290 align:middle line:84%
sense of connection with the
presence of the higher order

00:13:18.290 --> 00:13:20.510 align:middle line:90%
of being.

00:13:20.510 --> 00:13:23.360 align:middle line:84%
What you formerly believed,
it's gone out the window.

00:13:23.360 --> 00:13:28.320 align:middle line:90%


00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:32.070 align:middle line:84%
Your old identity has
begun to evaporate.

00:13:32.070 --> 00:13:34.770 align:middle line:84%
The new identity
hasn't emerged yet.

00:13:34.770 --> 00:13:38.670 align:middle line:84%
So you're in that
proverbial no man's land.

00:13:38.670 --> 00:13:41.910 align:middle line:84%
And that can last for
a short period of time,

00:13:41.910 --> 00:13:44.790 align:middle line:84%
or it can last for a
long period of time.

00:13:44.790 --> 00:13:47.095 align:middle line:84%
The dark night of
the soul, understand,

00:13:47.095 --> 00:13:48.720 align:middle line:84%
you don't have a dark
night of the soul

00:13:48.720 --> 00:13:51.330 align:middle line:84%
because someone died,
or you lost a job,

00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:52.210 align:middle line:90%
or you got a divorce.

00:13:52.210 --> 00:13:55.050 align:middle line:90%
That's regular sadness.

00:13:55.050 --> 00:13:57.120 align:middle line:84%
That's the sadness
of loss, and sadness

00:13:57.120 --> 00:14:00.810 align:middle line:84%
of somebody dying, the sadness
of a structure in your life.

00:14:00.810 --> 00:14:03.770 align:middle line:84%
Dark night of soul is
something different.

00:14:03.770 --> 00:14:06.490 align:middle line:84%
You could have nothing
wrong in your life,

00:14:06.490 --> 00:14:08.826 align:middle line:84%
and then suddenly,
there's a bereftness.

00:14:08.826 --> 00:14:12.340 align:middle line:84%
That generally means
that either through grace

00:14:12.340 --> 00:14:17.260 align:middle line:84%
or through spiritual practice,
your new identity is emerging.

00:14:17.260 --> 00:14:18.700 align:middle line:90%
But it hasn't emerged yet.

00:14:18.700 --> 00:14:20.180 align:middle line:84%
And you're not who
you used to be.

00:14:20.180 --> 00:14:21.430 align:middle line:90%
So you don't know who you are.

00:14:21.430 --> 00:14:22.972 align:middle line:84%
You don't even know
what you believe.

00:14:22.972 --> 00:14:27.883 align:middle line:84%
>> And so I realized really
early on in that day that I

00:14:27.883 --> 00:14:28.877 align:middle line:90%
couldn't think--

00:14:28.877 --> 00:14:31.362 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't spend all this
time and energy worrying

00:14:31.362 --> 00:14:35.215 align:middle line:84%
about what my future was going
to look like, because that

00:14:35.215 --> 00:14:36.132 align:middle line:90%
was just too far away.

00:14:36.132 --> 00:14:38.320 align:middle line:90%
It seemed insurmountable.

00:14:38.320 --> 00:14:40.805 align:middle line:84%
The prognosis from
the medical team,

00:14:40.805 --> 00:14:42.296 align:middle line:90%
it wasn't super optimistic.

00:14:42.296 --> 00:14:44.284 align:middle line:90%
They didn't know who I was.

00:14:44.284 --> 00:14:46.769 align:middle line:90%
They didn't know about my past.

00:14:46.769 --> 00:14:50.248 align:middle line:84%
They just had to prepare me as
best they could for my future.

00:14:50.248 --> 00:14:55.218 align:middle line:84%
So they said, you know, you
might not be able to run again.

00:14:55.218 --> 00:14:58.697 align:middle line:84%
You might not be
as active and be

00:14:58.697 --> 00:15:01.015 align:middle line:84%
able to do all
those crazy things

00:15:01.015 --> 00:15:03.667 align:middle line:84%
you like doing, like surfing
and rock-climbing and running.

00:15:03.667 --> 00:15:09.134 align:middle line:84%
But the reality is that
you'll probably drive again.

00:15:09.134 --> 00:15:10.443 align:middle line:90%
You'll probably get a job.

00:15:10.443 --> 00:15:13.110 align:middle line:84%
You'll probably go back to work,
and you might even get married.

00:15:13.110 --> 00:15:16.589 align:middle line:84%
And for me, I just
thought that was just--

00:15:16.589 --> 00:15:19.074 align:middle line:84%
I was so infuriated,
because I just thought,

00:15:19.074 --> 00:15:20.101 align:middle line:90%
you don't know who I am.

00:15:20.101 --> 00:15:21.559 align:middle line:84%
You don't know what
I'm capable of.

00:15:21.559 --> 00:15:23.050 align:middle line:90%
And I think--

00:15:23.050 --> 00:15:25.535 align:middle line:90%
I found that so infuriating.

00:15:25.535 --> 00:15:28.383 align:middle line:84%
It was that because
I'd had an accident--

00:15:28.383 --> 00:15:30.008 align:middle line:84%
I'd always been a
really high achiever.

00:15:30.008 --> 00:15:31.591 align:middle line:84%
I'd always done
really awesome things.

00:15:31.591 --> 00:15:34.450 align:middle line:84%
But because I'd had an accident,
suddenly the bar for me

00:15:34.450 --> 00:15:37.220 align:middle line:90%
was just placed right down here.

00:15:37.220 --> 00:15:39.050 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't like that.

00:15:39.050 --> 00:15:44.240 align:middle line:84%
>> And in the dark night, if
you can ask a question such

00:15:44.240 --> 00:15:51.510 align:middle line:84%
as, what quality do I need
to give birth to have peace

00:15:51.510 --> 00:15:55.160 align:middle line:84%
of mind if this were
to last forever?

00:15:55.160 --> 00:15:57.310 align:middle line:84%
You start to work with
something like that.

00:15:57.310 --> 00:15:58.970 align:middle line:90%
And why is it important?

00:15:58.970 --> 00:16:01.850 align:middle line:84%
Generally, when an individual
is in a dark night,

00:16:01.850 --> 00:16:04.850 align:middle line:84%
they go through
wishful thinking.

00:16:04.850 --> 00:16:07.040 align:middle line:90%
I wish I wasn't here.

00:16:07.040 --> 00:16:09.860 align:middle line:90%
I wish I wasn't who I was.

00:16:09.860 --> 00:16:11.700 align:middle line:84%
I wish I'd done
something differently.

00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:14.893 align:middle line:84%
I wish I'd made
different decisions.

00:16:14.893 --> 00:16:16.310 align:middle line:84%
It's a kind of a
wishful thinking.

00:16:16.310 --> 00:16:17.900 align:middle line:84%
None of those things
can ever happen

00:16:17.900 --> 00:16:20.090 align:middle line:84%
because you are who you
are, you are where you are,

00:16:20.090 --> 00:16:22.010 align:middle line:90%
and this is what's happening.

00:16:22.010 --> 00:16:24.530 align:middle line:84%
So to the degree that
you can pull yourself out

00:16:24.530 --> 00:16:29.720 align:middle line:84%
of wishful thinking and ask
a different kind of question,

00:16:29.720 --> 00:16:32.180 align:middle line:84%
when the dark night
is over, you've

00:16:32.180 --> 00:16:36.710 align:middle line:84%
found that you are a little bit
higher in your transformation

00:16:36.710 --> 00:16:39.770 align:middle line:84%
because you didn't waste the
time asking futile questions,

00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:40.820 align:middle line:90%
you see.

00:16:40.820 --> 00:16:43.820 align:middle line:84%
It's not something I would wish
upon anyone, the dark night.

00:16:43.820 --> 00:16:50.000 align:middle line:84%
However, every mystic,
in hindsight, loves it.

00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:52.590 align:middle line:84%
Because that was
the moment, that you

00:16:52.590 --> 00:16:54.620 align:middle line:84%
were in that crucial
bowl of darkness,

00:16:54.620 --> 00:16:57.510 align:middle line:90%
that crucible of transformation.

00:16:57.510 --> 00:17:00.750 align:middle line:84%
And what you gain from it
is that you could actually

00:17:00.750 --> 00:17:04.380 align:middle line:90%
see the light in the darkness.

00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:08.460 align:middle line:84%
The darkness shines
like the light.

00:17:08.460 --> 00:17:10.530 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, when
you come out of it,

00:17:10.530 --> 00:17:13.260 align:middle line:90%
you're really different.

00:17:13.260 --> 00:17:16.440 align:middle line:90%
You're more of yourself.

00:17:16.440 --> 00:17:19.670 align:middle line:84%
The mystic chord of
memory has been struck.

00:17:19.670 --> 00:17:21.890 align:middle line:84%
And you're remembering
who you are.

00:17:21.890 --> 00:17:25.020 align:middle line:84%
It has nothing to do with
a change of circumstance.

00:17:25.020 --> 00:17:30.030 align:middle line:84%
It's an expanded awareness
of the ineffable presence

00:17:30.030 --> 00:17:30.930 align:middle line:90%
that we all are.

00:17:30.930 --> 00:17:37.170 align:middle line:84%
>> And in a way, I was able
to use that as motivation.

00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:39.780 align:middle line:84%
But I remember when I got told
that, I thought, you know what?

00:17:39.780 --> 00:17:40.697 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to show you.

00:17:40.697 --> 00:17:43.670 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to do an
Ironman one day.

00:17:43.670 --> 00:17:45.790 align:middle line:84%
I've always had really
amazing people around me.

00:17:45.790 --> 00:17:49.690 align:middle line:84%
And I remember telling Michael,
my partner, and my mom,

00:17:49.690 --> 00:17:52.230 align:middle line:84%
well, I was like, I'm
going to do an Ironman.

00:17:52.230 --> 00:17:55.915 align:middle line:84%
They didn't say to
me, that's silly.

00:17:55.915 --> 00:17:57.790 align:middle line:84%
You've got to listen to
what the doctor said,

00:17:57.790 --> 00:17:59.200 align:middle line:90%
and that's unrealistic for you.

00:17:59.200 --> 00:18:01.870 align:middle line:84%
They just said,
oh, awesome idea.

00:18:01.870 --> 00:18:03.130 align:middle line:90%
Let's get you out.

00:18:03.130 --> 00:18:04.220 align:middle line:90%
Let's go get you training.

00:18:04.220 --> 00:18:05.970 align:middle line:84%
Let's go get you working
for this Ironman.

00:18:05.970 --> 00:18:10.450 align:middle line:90%


00:18:10.450 --> 00:18:13.182 align:middle line:84%
>> So when we do pick up the
phone and we answer that CTA,

00:18:13.182 --> 00:18:14.890 align:middle line:84%
that Call To Action
or Call To Adventure,

00:18:14.890 --> 00:18:17.380 align:middle line:84%
Joseph Campbell would say,
we crossed the threshold.

00:18:17.380 --> 00:18:19.810 align:middle line:84%
And we've officially
made the separation.

00:18:19.810 --> 00:18:22.430 align:middle line:84%
And we moved from the first
part into the second part,

00:18:22.430 --> 00:18:23.972 align:middle line:90%
which is now the initiation.

00:18:23.972 --> 00:18:25.930 align:middle line:84%
And this is where we're
going through the fire.

00:18:25.930 --> 00:18:27.058 align:middle line:90%
We start to meet allies.

00:18:27.058 --> 00:18:28.600 align:middle line:84%
We start to connect
with other people

00:18:28.600 --> 00:18:30.340 align:middle line:84%
who share our values,
the people who

00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:32.410 align:middle line:84%
stand for the same kind
of things we stand for,

00:18:32.410 --> 00:18:36.400 align:middle line:84%
the people who believe in
us and that we believe in.

00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:37.840 align:middle line:84%
The people that
are inspiring us.

00:18:37.840 --> 00:18:40.500 align:middle line:84%
The people that we want
along this journey,

00:18:40.500 --> 00:18:42.940 align:middle line:84%
that we want on
his ride with us.

00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:45.760 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time, we
start to fight our dragons.

00:18:45.760 --> 00:18:47.770 align:middle line:84%
And dragons can
be family members

00:18:47.770 --> 00:18:49.317 align:middle line:90%
that don't believe in us.

00:18:49.317 --> 00:18:51.400 align:middle line:84%
They can be friends that
we've had for a long time

00:18:51.400 --> 00:18:53.770 align:middle line:84%
that we think we need to
stay friends with just

00:18:53.770 --> 00:18:56.020 align:middle line:90%
because that's been so long.

00:18:56.020 --> 00:18:58.470 align:middle line:84%
It can be our own
personal beliefs

00:18:58.470 --> 00:19:01.620 align:middle line:84%
that we've had about ourselves
for a long time, to include,

00:19:01.620 --> 00:19:03.970 align:middle line:84%
I am not enough,
here I go again,

00:19:03.970 --> 00:19:05.290 align:middle line:90%
who am I to be doing this.

00:19:05.290 --> 00:19:08.620 align:middle line:84%
All of the self-doubt that
creeps in our minds, those

00:19:08.620 --> 00:19:09.580 align:middle line:90%
are the dragons.

00:19:09.580 --> 00:19:11.380 align:middle line:84%
So it's external
and internal dragons

00:19:11.380 --> 00:19:13.060 align:middle line:84%
that we fight going
through the fire.

00:19:13.060 --> 00:19:15.300 align:middle line:90%
We all have to experience that.

00:19:15.300 --> 00:19:19.010 align:middle line:84%
>> My partner Michael, he would
go out and buy me all of these

00:19:19.010 --> 00:19:19.810 align:middle line:90%
sports clothes.

00:19:19.810 --> 00:19:23.530 align:middle line:84%
These really inspiring slogans,
it was a little bit corny.

00:19:23.530 --> 00:19:26.300 align:middle line:90%
But things like "never give up."

00:19:26.300 --> 00:19:28.180 align:middle line:84%
So I'd be in this
little hospital

00:19:28.180 --> 00:19:30.700 align:middle line:84%
mask with this full
body compression suit

00:19:30.700 --> 00:19:33.680 align:middle line:84%
with these inspiring
slogans on the ceilings.

00:19:33.680 --> 00:19:35.050 align:middle line:90%
It sounds really corny.

00:19:35.050 --> 00:19:37.210 align:middle line:84%
But at the time,
I appreciated it

00:19:37.210 --> 00:19:39.340 align:middle line:84%
having these people
who so believed in me,

00:19:39.340 --> 00:19:40.810 align:middle line:90%
who so wanted me to get better.

00:19:40.810 --> 00:19:45.250 align:middle line:90%


00:19:45.250 --> 00:19:48.730 align:middle line:84%
It was so beautiful of them
to show up for me every day

00:19:48.730 --> 00:19:49.740 align:middle line:90%
consistently.

00:19:49.740 --> 00:19:51.490 align:middle line:84%
And be there, even if
I was in a bad mood,

00:19:51.490 --> 00:19:53.380 align:middle line:84%
even if I didn't
feel strong that day,

00:19:53.380 --> 00:19:55.360 align:middle line:84%
even if I felt really
overwhelmed by what

00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:56.590 align:middle line:90%
I was doing.

00:19:56.590 --> 00:19:59.440 align:middle line:84%
They were there with
me every single day.

00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:01.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Once you start
walking down this path,

00:20:01.540 --> 00:20:04.780 align:middle line:90%
people will talk about you.

00:20:04.780 --> 00:20:05.980 align:middle line:90%
And you're afraid.

00:20:05.980 --> 00:20:07.188 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid I'm going to fail.

00:20:07.188 --> 00:20:08.605 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid it's
not going to work.

00:20:08.605 --> 00:20:10.520 align:middle line:84%
People are going to
laugh at me if I fail.

00:20:10.520 --> 00:20:16.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you do fail, which is
the learning, people will talk.

00:20:16.300 --> 00:20:18.300 align:middle line:84%
If you succeed, they're
going to talk about you.

00:20:18.300 --> 00:20:20.600 align:middle line:84%
They're going to talk
about you either way

00:20:20.600 --> 00:20:23.660 align:middle line:84%
because mediocrity
attacks excellence.

00:20:23.660 --> 00:20:26.180 align:middle line:84%
Knowing that you're going to
be talked about either way,

00:20:26.180 --> 00:20:29.090 align:middle line:84%
you don't live your life
with what other people are

00:20:29.090 --> 00:20:31.910 align:middle line:90%
thinking as your consideration.

