If it's not, then our career
can support the calling.

00:41:45.850 --> 00:41:51.180 align:middle line:84%
Without an answering of the
calling, our soul is bereft.

00:41:51.180 --> 00:41:56.490 align:middle line:90%
It's sad, it's morose.

00:41:56.490 --> 00:42:00.290 align:middle line:84%
And so I think our path
is to find our calling,

00:42:00.290 --> 00:42:02.550 align:middle line:90%
and to answer it.

00:42:02.550 --> 00:42:05.650 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes the job you have
or the career you have

00:42:05.650 --> 00:42:06.450 align:middle line:90%
is your calling.

00:42:06.450 --> 00:42:08.110 align:middle line:90%
Many times it's not.

00:42:08.110 --> 00:42:12.350 align:middle line:84%
Many times, your career, your
job supports your calling.

00:42:12.350 --> 00:42:14.760 align:middle line:84%
And so then you
have a nice paradox

00:42:14.760 --> 00:42:16.790 align:middle line:84%
of the job or the career
supporting the calling.

00:42:16.790 --> 00:42:19.850 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing
wrong with that either.

00:42:19.850 --> 00:42:22.960 align:middle line:84%
>> But we're indoctrinating
people to believe, oh,

00:42:22.960 --> 00:42:25.060 align:middle line:84%
being that waitress is
beneath you because, see,

00:42:25.060 --> 00:42:28.270 align:middle line:84%
your purpose is to be the
artist or the musician.

00:42:28.270 --> 00:42:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And if it's really your
purpose, it'll pay.

00:42:30.160 --> 00:42:33.080 align:middle line:90%


00:42:33.080 --> 00:42:37.280 align:middle line:84%
>> I can remember a gentleman
that was very pressured

00:42:37.280 --> 00:42:39.530 align:middle line:90%
into becoming a doctor.

00:42:39.530 --> 00:42:42.330 align:middle line:84%
His father was a doctor, his
grandfather was a doctor.

00:42:42.330 --> 00:42:45.560 align:middle line:84%
And so it was just assumed
he would go into medicine.

00:42:45.560 --> 00:42:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And he did until he
suffered from cancer.

00:42:50.580 --> 00:42:53.360 align:middle line:84%
And in the process of
healing the cancer,

00:42:53.360 --> 00:42:57.080 align:middle line:84%
he fell back in love with
his passion, which was music.

00:42:57.080 --> 00:42:59.360 align:middle line:90%
He was a violinist.

00:42:59.360 --> 00:43:03.970 align:middle line:84%
And when he shifted
over to his love

00:43:03.970 --> 00:43:06.290 align:middle line:84%
he not only healed his
cancer but he found

00:43:06.290 --> 00:43:08.270 align:middle line:90%
his calling, which was music.

00:43:08.270 --> 00:43:12.080 align:middle line:84%
He was able to transcend
the parental fantasy.

00:43:12.080 --> 00:43:14.210 align:middle line:84%
And of course, it didn't
come without struggle

00:43:14.210 --> 00:43:16.940 align:middle line:90%
of the soul, pain of the body.

00:43:16.940 --> 00:43:18.290 align:middle line:90%
But he ultimately did.

00:43:18.290 --> 00:43:21.490 align:middle line:90%


00:43:21.490 --> 00:43:26.470 align:middle line:84%
>> This is really important
because the new age media

00:43:26.470 --> 00:43:31.020 align:middle line:84%
paints purpose, Dharma, as
though somehow you're going

00:43:31.020 --> 00:43:36.280 align:middle line:84%
to find yourself on the cover of
a magazine when you figure out

00:43:36.280 --> 00:43:39.130 align:middle line:84%
what your purpose is and you
actually live it and fulfill

00:43:39.130 --> 00:43:39.930 align:middle line:90%
it.

00:43:39.930 --> 00:43:42.520 align:middle line:84%
Because you're going to
be the most famous that,

00:43:42.520 --> 00:43:46.590 align:middle line:84%
the best this, the richest
that, the newest this.

00:43:46.590 --> 00:43:48.610 align:middle line:90%
Maybe sometimes.

00:43:48.610 --> 00:43:53.960 align:middle line:84%
Maybe some people, maybe
that's some people's Dharma.

00:43:53.960 --> 00:43:57.890 align:middle line:90%
But it's not, not most people's.

00:43:57.890 --> 00:44:01.670 align:middle line:84%
And to really stay
rooted in what's

00:44:01.670 --> 00:44:06.230 align:middle line:84%
in alignment with
the core of who I am,

00:44:06.230 --> 00:44:08.390 align:middle line:90%
and to move forward with that.

00:44:08.390 --> 00:44:11.750 align:middle line:84%
And when we know who we are
we will know what to do.

00:44:11.750 --> 00:44:15.330 align:middle line:90%


00:44:15.330 --> 00:44:18.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Finding your purpose
comes down to two things.

00:44:18.490 --> 00:44:22.650 align:middle line:84%
The first one is, dropping
from the head into the heart.

00:44:22.650 --> 00:44:25.240 align:middle line:84%
And the best way to do
that is through meditation

00:44:25.240 --> 00:44:26.040 align:middle line:90%
and mindfulness.

00:44:26.040 --> 00:44:30.600 align:middle line:84%
And actually, taking the time
to be quiet and to listen.

00:44:30.600 --> 00:44:33.060 align:middle line:84%
>> You establish your
intention to wake up,

00:44:33.060 --> 00:44:36.510 align:middle line:84%
to expand your awareness
to who and what you are.

00:44:36.510 --> 00:44:38.970 align:middle line:84%
And so the moment
of meditation is

00:44:38.970 --> 00:44:42.060 align:middle line:84%
when you have that moment
of connectedness to life,

00:44:42.060 --> 00:44:46.090 align:middle line:84%
and you learn how to pay
undistractable attention to it.

00:44:46.090 --> 00:44:50.970 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is,
all manner of debris,

00:44:50.970 --> 00:44:54.300 align:middle line:84%
thought forms, whatever it may
be flowing through your mind--

00:44:54.300 --> 00:44:58.260 align:middle line:84%
but you're learning to have
dominion over your attention

00:44:58.260 --> 00:45:00.690 align:middle line:84%
so that as the
insight is occurring,

00:45:00.690 --> 00:45:03.060 align:middle line:84%
you're able to be
aware of it and have

00:45:03.060 --> 00:45:05.520 align:middle line:84%
a level of
stabilization around it.

00:45:05.520 --> 00:45:06.960 align:middle line:90%
You meditate on your existence.

00:45:06.960 --> 00:45:07.770 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

00:45:07.770 --> 00:45:08.800 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:45:08.800 --> 00:45:09.870 align:middle line:90%
The Ws.

00:45:09.870 --> 00:45:10.780 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:45:10.780 --> 00:45:11.580 align:middle line:90%
Why am I?

00:45:11.580 --> 00:45:12.840 align:middle line:90%
Where am I?

00:45:12.840 --> 00:45:14.520 align:middle line:90%
When am I?

00:45:14.520 --> 00:45:16.995 align:middle line:84%
Until you start to be
taught, not just a belief,

00:45:16.995 --> 00:45:18.870 align:middle line:84%
but you start to
have an insight.

00:45:18.870 --> 00:45:20.305 align:middle line:90%
So that's existential.

00:45:20.305 --> 00:45:21.930 align:middle line:84%
And spiritual meditation
is when you're

00:45:21.930 --> 00:45:25.140 align:middle line:90%
meditating simply to wake up.

00:45:25.140 --> 00:45:28.965 align:middle line:84%
You're establishing your
intention to wake up,

00:45:28.965 --> 00:45:30.840 align:middle line:84%
to have a greater
realization of your oneness

00:45:30.840 --> 00:45:34.980 align:middle line:84%
with life, whether you call
life god, or the presence,

00:45:34.980 --> 00:45:37.070 align:middle line:90%
of love, or intelligence.

00:45:37.070 --> 00:45:41.040 align:middle line:84%
But whatever the technique
is, it's fundamental.

00:45:41.040 --> 00:45:43.030 align:middle line:90%
It's fundamental.

00:45:43.030 --> 00:45:48.840 align:middle line:84%
And then affirmative prayer
is not begging or beseeching.

00:45:48.840 --> 00:45:53.640 align:middle line:84%
You're actually praying to
have a realization of what

00:45:53.640 --> 00:45:54.990 align:middle line:90%
you're praying for.

00:45:54.990 --> 00:45:58.080 align:middle line:90%
You already have it, you see.

00:45:58.080 --> 00:46:02.170 align:middle line:84%
We enter into a
state of gratitude.

00:46:02.170 --> 00:46:06.636 align:middle line:84%
And then we begin to recognize
the presence that's everywhere.

00:46:06.636 --> 00:46:10.200 align:middle line:84%
We begin to feel our
unity with this presence.

00:46:10.200 --> 00:46:13.650 align:middle line:84%
And then we proclaim
or declare what

00:46:13.650 --> 00:46:17.700 align:middle line:84%
is so, whether it's about
our abundance or our health.

00:46:17.700 --> 00:46:20.160 align:middle line:84%
We give thanks that
it's already done.

00:46:20.160 --> 00:46:21.645 align:middle line:90%
And we release it into the law.

00:46:21.645 --> 00:46:24.760 align:middle line:90%
It becomes our new law of being.

00:46:24.760 --> 00:46:26.920 align:middle line:84%
>> The quality of our life
depends upon the quality

00:46:26.920 --> 00:46:28.880 align:middle line:84%
of the questions
we ask ourselves.

00:46:28.880 --> 00:46:31.638 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that when someone
asks, what is my purpose?

00:46:31.638 --> 00:46:33.430 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things
am I passionate about?

00:46:33.430 --> 00:46:34.960 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things
am I great at?

00:46:34.960 --> 00:46:37.390 align:middle line:84%
What do I feel a
connection to in the world?

00:46:37.390 --> 00:46:38.927 align:middle line:84%
If asking what
are you passionate

00:46:38.927 --> 00:46:40.510 align:middle line:84%
about doesn't resonate
with you, there

00:46:40.510 --> 00:46:43.060 align:middle line:84%
are so many deeper
questions we can ask.

00:46:43.060 --> 00:46:45.250 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of
things do you enjoy?

00:46:45.250 --> 00:46:47.170 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things
are you curious about?

00:46:47.170 --> 00:46:48.540 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things
are you interested in?

00:46:48.540 --> 00:46:50.560 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things
did you like as a child,

00:46:50.560 --> 00:46:52.420 align:middle line:84%
do you remember really
enjoying as a child,

00:46:52.420 --> 00:46:54.170 align:middle line:84%
that you maybe haven't
even thought about,

00:46:54.170 --> 00:46:57.040 align:middle line:84%
like playing the guitar,
the piano, or singing?

00:46:57.040 --> 00:46:58.620 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things
bring you joy?

00:46:58.620 --> 00:47:00.370 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things
makes you come alive?

00:47:00.370 --> 00:47:02.650 align:middle line:84%
What kinds of things, when
you think about doing,

00:47:02.650 --> 00:47:04.060 align:middle line:90%
make you smile?

00:47:04.060 --> 00:47:06.050 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's down the path
of entrepreneurship.

00:47:06.050 --> 00:47:08.770 align:middle line:84%
But maybe just by getting
clear on what your purpose is,

00:47:08.770 --> 00:47:12.310 align:middle line:84%
you find an organization,
a company, a nonprofit,

00:47:12.310 --> 00:47:15.490 align:middle line:84%
some kind of entity that
aligns with those same values.

00:47:15.490 --> 00:47:17.830 align:middle line:84%
And there's really no better
answer than intuitively

00:47:17.830 --> 00:47:19.690 align:middle line:90%
and energetically we feel that.

00:47:19.690 --> 00:47:26.592 align:middle line:90%


00:47:26.592 --> 00:47:31.540 align:middle line:90%
[WAVES LAPPING]

00:47:31.540 --> 00:47:34.540 align:middle line:84%
>> One morning, an old man
is walking on the beach.

00:47:34.540 --> 00:47:37.920 align:middle line:90%


00:47:37.920 --> 00:47:41.460 align:middle line:84%
And he looks down and sees
in the distance what looks

00:47:41.460 --> 00:47:45.438 align:middle line:90%
like a dancing silhouette.

00:47:45.438 --> 00:47:47.980 align:middle line:84%
As he gets closer, he realizes
it's not a dancing silhouette.

00:47:47.980 --> 00:47:49.730 align:middle line:90%
It's actually a little boy.

00:47:49.730 --> 00:47:51.480 align:middle line:84%
And what the little
boy is doing is

00:47:51.480 --> 00:47:53.520 align:middle line:84%
he's picking starfish
up from the beach

00:47:53.520 --> 00:47:56.610 align:middle line:84%
and he's throwing them into
the ocean one at a time.

00:47:56.610 --> 00:47:58.890 align:middle line:84%
Picking up a starfish and
throwing it in the ocean.

00:47:58.890 --> 00:48:02.220 align:middle line:90%


00:48:02.220 --> 00:48:03.980 align:middle line:84%
And the old man, he's
lived a rough life.

00:48:03.980 --> 00:48:06.365 align:middle line:84%
He sees things a certain
way, a little bit cynical.

00:48:06.365 --> 00:48:08.316 align:middle line:90%


00:48:08.316 --> 00:48:11.150 align:middle line:84%
He was like, boy,
what are you doing?

00:48:11.150 --> 00:48:15.130 align:middle line:84%
And the boy says, you
can't see what's happening?

00:48:15.130 --> 00:48:18.580 align:middle line:84%
He said, the sun's out
in the middle of the sky,

00:48:18.580 --> 00:48:20.200 align:middle line:90%
the tide's gone out.

00:48:20.200 --> 00:48:23.237 align:middle line:84%
There's starfish
lining the beach.

00:48:23.237 --> 00:48:25.570 align:middle line:84%
And if I don't pick them up
and throw them in the ocean,

00:48:25.570 --> 00:48:26.510 align:middle line:90%
they're going to die.

00:48:26.510 --> 00:48:27.885 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
burn up and die.

00:48:27.885 --> 00:48:30.100 align:middle line:90%


00:48:30.100 --> 00:48:32.410 align:middle line:84%
And the old man looks
and says, boy, there's

00:48:32.410 --> 00:48:35.110 align:middle line:84%
miles of beach this way,
miles of beach that way.

00:48:35.110 --> 00:48:38.560 align:middle line:84%
There's thousands if not tens
of thousands of starfish.

00:48:38.560 --> 00:48:43.850 align:middle line:84%
You can't possibly
make a difference.

00:48:43.850 --> 00:48:49.410 align:middle line:84%
And little boy picks up
a starfish, throws it in.

00:48:49.410 --> 00:48:53.860 align:middle line:90%


00:48:53.860 --> 00:48:56.546 align:middle line:84%
It made a difference
to that one.

00:48:56.546 --> 00:49:00.030 align:middle line:84%
And I think the story is a
powerful illustration of, yes,

00:49:00.030 --> 00:49:01.683 align:middle line:84%
there are miles
of beach this way

00:49:01.683 --> 00:49:02.850 align:middle line:90%
and miles of beach that way.

00:49:02.850 --> 00:49:07.435 align:middle line:84%
There are countless challenges,
environmental, social,

00:49:07.435 --> 00:49:08.310 align:middle line:90%
financial, political.

00:49:08.310 --> 00:49:10.380 align:middle line:84%
So many challenges
our world is facing.

00:49:10.380 --> 00:49:13.518 align:middle line:84%
And yet, most people will
be the old man and say,

00:49:13.518 --> 00:49:15.060 align:middle line:84%
you can't possibly
make a difference.

00:49:15.060 --> 00:49:16.710 align:middle line:90%
Why even try?

00:49:16.710 --> 00:49:19.620 align:middle line:84%
And yet, there are some of us,
and there are more and more.

00:49:19.620 --> 00:49:21.990 align:middle line:84%
There's this community is
growing of people who are just

00:49:21.990 --> 00:49:22.800 align:middle line:90%
going to say, you know what?

00:49:22.800 --> 00:49:25.560 align:middle line:84%
Let me pick up what my starfish
is to pick up and throw in.

00:49:25.560 --> 00:49:28.240 align:middle line:90%


00:49:28.240 --> 00:49:32.620 align:middle line:84%
>> In brain research, it's shown
that compassion shifts brain

00:49:32.620 --> 00:49:35.140 align:middle line:84%
function more than
anything else.

00:49:35.140 --> 00:49:37.630 align:middle line:84%
And what's been happening
over the last 300 years,

00:49:37.630 --> 00:49:41.110 align:middle line:84%
in just a few decades
we reversed position

00:49:41.110 --> 00:49:45.670 align:middle line:84%
globally on slavery, on
democracy, on women's rights,

00:49:45.670 --> 00:49:47.170 align:middle line:90%
on child labor.

00:49:47.170 --> 00:49:51.700 align:middle line:84%
We've become more, and more, and
more compassionate as a species

00:49:51.700 --> 00:49:53.897 align:middle line:90%
for the last few hundred years.

00:49:53.897 --> 00:49:55.105 align:middle line:90%
And it's changing our brains.

00:49:55.105 --> 00:49:55.905 align:middle line:90%


00:49:55.905 --> 00:49:58.060 align:middle line:84%
>> There's this fascinating
study that was done,

00:49:58.060 --> 00:50:01.120 align:middle line:84%
and a term that was coined,
called the overview effect.

00:50:01.120 --> 00:50:04.930 align:middle line:84%
Which is, when astronauts go to
outer space and they come back,

00:50:04.930 --> 00:50:08.142 align:middle line:84%
their families and their friends
start to go, something changed.

00:50:08.142 --> 00:50:10.600 align:middle line:84%
Fundamentally, there's something
different about this human

00:50:10.600 --> 00:50:11.290 align:middle line:90%
being.

00:50:11.290 --> 00:50:13.207 align:middle line:84%
And as they've done these
longitudinal studies

00:50:13.207 --> 00:50:15.760 align:middle line:84%
on astronauts and figuring
out what exactly shifted,

00:50:15.760 --> 00:50:18.430 align:middle line:84%
they came up with this term
called the overview effect.

00:50:18.430 --> 00:50:20.320 align:middle line:90%
What it boils down to is this.

00:50:20.320 --> 00:50:22.570 align:middle line:84%
When you're in space
looking down on the Earth,

00:50:22.570 --> 00:50:27.190 align:middle line:84%
you see the Earth as a
living, breathing organism.

00:50:27.190 --> 00:50:30.850 align:middle line:84%
And we, as humans, as
part of this organism,

00:50:30.850 --> 00:50:33.070 align:middle line:90%
are like the cells in our body.

00:50:33.070 --> 00:50:35.920 align:middle line:84%
We are a small part of
a much bigger puzzle.

00:50:35.920 --> 00:50:38.532 align:middle line:84%
And yet, just like we
need every single cell

00:50:38.532 --> 00:50:40.990 align:middle line:84%
to come together to make tissue,
and tissue to make organs,

00:50:40.990 --> 00:50:44.500 align:middle line:84%
and organs to make up the
body, every single human being,

00:50:44.500 --> 00:50:46.210 align:middle line:84%
when they're alive
and on purpose,

00:50:46.210 --> 00:50:49.060 align:middle line:84%
gets to be the cell that is
functioning at its highest

00:50:49.060 --> 00:50:51.760 align:middle line:84%
capacity in order to
make this organism, which

00:50:51.760 --> 00:50:52.780 align:middle line:90%
is planet Earth.

00:50:52.780 --> 00:50:54.700 align:middle line:84%
They see it as a
living, breathing being.

00:50:54.700 --> 00:50:55.980 align:middle line:90%
We're just a part of it.

00:50:55.980 --> 00:50:57.730 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's a great
opportunity for us

00:50:57.730 --> 00:51:01.722 align:middle line:84%
to feel insignificant
and extremely significant

00:51:01.722 --> 00:51:02.680 align:middle line:90%
at the exact same time.

00:51:02.680 --> 00:51:05.170 align:middle line:84%
Whether we pick up that starfish
and put it in the ocean,

00:51:05.170 --> 00:51:07.070 align:middle line:84%
whether we step
into our purpose,

00:51:07.070 --> 00:51:09.130 align:middle line:84%
whether we do what
we're here to do,

00:51:09.130 --> 00:51:11.200 align:middle line:84%
every single one of
those cells needs

00:51:11.200 --> 00:51:13.100 align:middle line:84%
to be functioning
the best possible way

00:51:13.100 --> 00:51:15.100 align:middle line:84%
that it can be in order
for the whole to operate

00:51:15.100 --> 00:51:16.017 align:middle line:90%
the way that needs to.

00:51:16.017 --> 00:51:17.488 align:middle line:90%


00:51:17.488 --> 00:51:19.280 align:middle line:84%
>> We have all these
problems in the world.

00:51:19.280 --> 00:51:20.730 align:middle line:90%
We have global warming.

00:51:20.730 --> 00:51:23.130 align:middle line:84%
We have weaponized
artificial intelligence

00:51:23.130 --> 00:51:26.040 align:middle line:84%
that's threatening to
produce all kinds of problems

00:51:26.040 --> 00:51:28.770 align:middle line:84%
among societies and
between nations.

00:51:28.770 --> 00:51:31.080 align:middle line:84%
We have human trafficking,
we have civil wars,

00:51:31.080 --> 00:51:32.167 align:middle line:90%
we have all these things.

00:51:32.167 --> 00:51:34.500 align:middle line:84%
We look at the world and say,
those things are terrible.

00:51:34.500 --> 00:51:35.970 align:middle line:90%
How do we solve them?

00:51:35.970 --> 00:51:39.980 align:middle line:84%
But research shows that
in these blissful states,

00:51:39.980 --> 00:51:43.690 align:middle line:84%
in these ecstatic states, they
don't just make us feel better

00:51:43.690 --> 00:51:45.810 align:middle line:84%
and they don't just
extend to meditation.

00:51:45.810 --> 00:51:48.870 align:middle line:84%
